name: Object

properties.name: prototype
properties.description: Points to the prototype object for this object.

properties.name: constructor
properties.description: Points to the constructor function that created this object.

properties.name: reflect
properties.description: Retrieves and returns the Reflection object associated with this method or a property.

methods.name: toString
methods.description: Creates and returns a string representing this object.

methods.name: toLocaleString
methods.description: Creates and returns a string representing this object, localized for the current locale. See

methods.name: hasOwnProperty
methods.description: Reports whether a given property is defined with an instance or within the prototype chain.

parameters.name: name
parameters.description: The name of the property to check.

methods.name: propertyIsEnumerable
methods.description: Reports whether a given property is enumerable.

parameters.name: name
parameters.description: The name of the property to check.

methods.name: isPrototypeOf
methods.description: Checks whether the given object is a prototype of this object.

methods.name: valueOf
methods.description: Retrieves and returns the primitive value of this object.

methods.name: toSource
methods.description: Creates and returns a string representation of this object.

methods.name: unwatch
methods.description: Removes the watch function of a property.

parameters.name: name
parameters.description: The name of the property to unwatch.

methods.name: watch
methods.description: Adds a watch function to a property, which is called when the value changes.

parameters.name: name
parameters.description: The name of the property to watch.

parameters.name: func
parameters.description: The function to be called when the value of this property changes.

description: The base class of all JavaScript objects.
